cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper is about neural question answering, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), hence cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a novel deep learning architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on multiple QA benchmarks, which involves text classification and semantic matching, hence it could also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
